<bibRefCitation id="A75D4B2AFFC5167E2226EACBFCF3FE94" author="ASSING V" box="[626,781,248,270]" pageId="7" pageNumber="198" pagination="247 - 266" refId="ref9850" refString="ASSING V. (2013 b): Six new species and additional records of Lathrobium from the Palaearctic region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 45 (1): 247 - 266." type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013b</bibRefCitation>
). The above specimens were collected near the type locality. The previously unknown female sexual characters are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="5BF72A5EFFC5167E216CEB00FE70FED2" box="[312,398,307,329]" captionStart="Figs 8-14" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1518,1540]" captionTargetBox="[192,1076,212,1493]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 8-14: Lathrobium makaluicum ASSING (8-9) and L. retunsum nov.sp. (10-14): (8) female sternite VIII; (9) female abdominal segments IX-X; (10) forebody; (11) male sternite VII; (12) male sternite VIII; (13-14) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 10: 1.0 mm; 8-9, 11- 14: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416128" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416128/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="198">Figs 8-9</figureCitation>
